8





447 Great Mall DrMilpitas, CA 95035


        (408) 934-9547
    






#41

I received the best customer service today at the New York & Company store located at the Great Mall in Milpitas.  

I was shopping around for some tops, leggings and pants and I popped into New York & Company because they sent me a coupon for my birthday last week.  I thought to myself, "Shoot, I have no problem creating an excuse to go shopping for new clothes," so off I went.

I was perusing the store and looking for my size and a young lady asked me if I needed any help finding my look or my size.  I usually do not ask for help, but I am not too familiar with this store so the offer for assistance was warmly welcomed.  

I shared with her that I needed a 4 "regular" and all I could find were either "tall" or "petite" or larger sizes so I thought I was out of luck.  She looked and we did not find my size, so she quickly offered me a different fitting pant.  She found exactly what I was looking for, even though I did not know it until I tried her suggestion.  Perfect fit!  And this was a look I have never tried.  

As I was in the dressing room trying on other items, she knocked on the door and shared with me that she had found a smaller size in the original pant I wanted to try and did I want to see if they fit.  I thought, "No, they will be too tight," But she was persistent that I should try, so I acquiesced and decided to try her suggestion.  

Wow! Was I happy I did--another perfect fit.

It is not often that I like everything I take into a dressing room, but today was a wonderful "win" in the clothing department.

When I arrived at the register to pay, the girl working the register rang me up, I paid and then a little note came up on the credit/debit machine that read something about: "Look for your birthday discount" and it was at that moment I remembered my discount birthday card that New York & Company sent me last week, daaaaang ;(

The cashier told me that those discounts do not apply to "previous purchases" and I could not use it, but I thought, "That is kind of weird, since the 'previous purchase' was less than 15 seconds ago, why can she not delete my purchase and apply my discount?"  She called for her manager, Anna, and that is when the wonderful girl who helped me in the back came up and totally solved the problem--in less than one minute.  

Not only is Anna the best clothing consultant, she is the greatest manager too.  Thank you Anna for your kindness, wonderful attitude and great fashion sense, I have decided to become a New York & Company regular because of you--at the Milpitas location--even though it took me an hour to drive there.  Service, like the service provided to me by Anna, is worth a long drive.  

Stephani Smiles for New York & Company and Anna ;)
#askforannaandshewillhookyuouup







This is a great outlet store to get your business causal and just business attire! The store seems to be always on some kind of sale since it is an outlet store. It's a pretty decent sized store that caters to all your business attire needs! They offer items from dress shirts, cardigans, dresses, dress pants and also some causal attire like t-shirts. 

Just a note: their sizing is a little different. I usually wear a M for dress shirts but for some reason, a XS fits perfectly and a S is a little loose on me. So I guess their clothing runs big. But! That's only for the dress shirts. I have yet to try their other clothing. 

I would definitely be coming back because it's a great place to get your typical work clothes at an affordable price.







I have a love hate relationship with NY&C. I always seem to find really good deals online and then I spend all my money...then I feel sad and happy all at the same time. Today I stumbled into the store and was greeted by a very friendly employee. She told me about the extra % off for all items and an extra 25% on clearance. Well I beelined to the clearance and found myself a cute sweater and new work pants! All for $30-ish dollars...what a steal!

It's just a shame that they don't order things by size at all. So unless you have the time or patience to sift through racks of clothes, I probably wouldn't be back. I was just lucky to find the items I did.







New York and Company specializes mainly in women's business attire. This location is more of an outlet, so the clothes are well-priced -- especially when you manage to walk in on a store-wide sale. Today, NY&C was on its last day of the Columbus Weekend Sale, and I made sure to take full advantage of the mark-downs.

One of the best things about shopping at the Great Mall's NY&C has to be the amazing service the staff provides. While I did not manage to catch the names of the girls that assisted me, they have my eternal gratitude for helping make my day's shopping experience wonderful. 

The staff will ensure that your time spent in the store is pain-free. They will offer to take your items and reserve a dressing room for you. When you're trying things on in the dressing room, they frequently stop by to see if you need a different size or color. 

In addition to having an awesome staff, the store's layout is incredibly well organized. Clothing is easy to find, and there's always a multitude of sizes. Also, since NY&C's focus is women's business attire, you can pick up all your fashion essentials (skirt, pants, blouse, blazer, dress, etc) here. 

All-in-all, today's experience  has guaranteed my continued patronage.







Can you say no place to wait awful customer service ?   So you go to buy clothes and while you are waiting for your partner to try on clothes you sit on the floor.  They tell you not allowed.  Hummm.  Why ?  We can't.  I guess it's their store and hence their policies but this one is plain dumb.







How are you not going to have cash in your register & on a holiday weekend like Mother's day? I've worked in retail & know your susposed to have back up change. Not leave your cash paying customes waiting in line while you run to the bank to get change.







I'd never before shopped in a New York & Co outlet Store. I was surprised that the prices weren't lower. Sweaters for $20 in an outlet the day after Christmas wasn't the best deal in town. The jewelry was all marked down to $5.99 each but that wasn't something that I haven't seen before in their regular store. 
All in all, it was a nice shopping experience with very pleasant employees but the prices were much higher than I expected. 
The store was very neat and well lite but I was expecting lower prices.







New York and Company is the WORST company I have ever dealt with,  Eastridge mall in San Jose the worst store. After battling months of chronic fatigue that left me bed rodden, then a viral infection that lasted 2 months.  I was finally physically able to go and return items I had order January 6, 2016. They refused to put the credit back on my card and only offered store credit.  When I ask if they could call customer service for me they said they can't call but they would give me a number to call. Of course the number was bogus and didn't allow you to speak with anyone.  I looked on the back of my platinum card and called customer service.  The person I talked with JENNY on4/4/16 said I could have the merchandise recredited to my account and she would speak with whomever was helping me, I put it on speaker and she told the girl to refill me and she would stay on the line and walk her through whatever steps so it would go through.  Then she told the sales girl she could give me a merchandise credit! The whole reason why I called platinum customer service was because I wanted it recredited to my account.  If this is how New York and Company treats people that are disabled they shouldn't be in business!  What's worse I have been shopping thete over 30 years.  Macy's is a must have better bet for customer service and appreciation. DO NOT SHOP THERE!







            New York & Company
        






