#41I received the best customer service today at the New York & Company store located at the Great Mall in Milpitas.  I was shopping around for some tops, leggings and pants and I popped into New York & Company because they sent me a coupon for my birthday last week.  I thought to myself, "Shoot, I have no problem creating an excuse to go shopping for new clothes," so off I went.I was perusing the store and looking for my size and a young lady asked me if I needed any help finding my look or my size.  I usually do not ask for help, but I am not too familiar with this store so the offer for assistance was warmly welcomed.  I shared with her that I needed a 4 "regular" and all I could find were either "tall" or "petite" or larger sizes so I thought I was out of luck.  She looked and we did not find my size, so she quickly offered me a different fitting pant.  She found exactly what I was looking for, even though I did not know it until I tried her suggestion.  Perfect fit!  And this was a look I have never tried.  As I was in the dressing room trying on other items, she knocked on the door and shared with me that she had found a smaller size in the original pant I wanted to try and did I want to see if they fit.  I thought, "No, they will be too tight," But she was persistent that I should try, so I acquiesced and decided to try her suggestion.  Wow! Was I happy I did--another perfect fit.It is not often that I like everything I take into a dressing room, but today was a wonderful "win" in the clothing department.When I arrived at the register to pay, the girl working the register rang me up, I paid and then a little note came up on the credit/debit machine that read something about: "Look for your birthday discount" and it was at that moment I remembered my discount birthday card that New York & Company sent me last week, daaaaang ;(The cashier told me that those discounts do not apply to "previous purchases" and I could not use it, but I thought, "That is kind of weird, since the 'previous purchase' was less than 15 seconds ago, why can she not delete my purchase and apply my discount?"  She called for her manager, Anna, and that is when the wonderful girl who helped me in the back came up and totally solved the problem--in less than one minute.  Not only is Anna the best clothing consultant, she is the greatest manager too.  Thank you Anna for your kindness, wonderful attitude and great fashion sense, I have decided to become a New York & Company regular because of you--at the Milpitas location--even though it took me an hour to drive there.  Service, like the service provided to me by Anna, is worth a long drive.  Stephani Smiles for New York & Company and Anna ;)#askforannaandshewillhookyuouup




