I have a love hate relationship with NY&C. I always seem to find really good deals online and then I spend all my money...then I feel sad and happy all at the same time. Today I stumbled into the store and was greeted by a very friendly employee. She told me about the extra % off for all items and an extra 25% on clearance. Well I beelined to the clearance and found myself a cute sweater and new work pants! All for $30-ish dollars...what a steal!It's just a shame that they don't order things by size at all. So unless you have the time or patience to sift through racks of clothes, I probably wouldn't be back. I was just lucky to find the items I did.




