        4/4/2016
    

New York and Company is the WORST company I have ever dealt with,  Eastridge mall in San Jose the worst store. After battling months of chronic fatigue that left me bed rodden, then a viral infection that lasted 2 months.  I was finally physically able to go and return items I had order January 6, 2016. They refused to put the credit back on my card and only offered store credit.  When I ask if they could call customer service for me they said they can't call but they would give me a number to call. Of course the number was bogus and didn't allow you to speak with anyone.  I looked on the back of my platinum card and called customer service.  The person I talked with JENNY on4/4/16 said I could have the merchandise recredited to my account and she would speak with whomever was helping me, I put it on speaker and she told the girl to refill me and she would stay on the line and walk her through whatever steps so it would go through.  Then she told the sales girl she could give me a merchandise credit! The whole reason why I called platinum customer service was because I wanted it recredited to my account.  If this is how New York and Company treats people that are disabled they shouldn't be in business!  What's worse I have been shopping thete over 30 years.  Macy's is a must have better bet for customer service and appreciation. DO NOT SHOP THERE!




