13





380 Eastridge MallSan Jose, CA 95122


        (408) 274-3535
    






Now that I'm all grown up, my standards have changed. I used to be content with cheap, trendy, and easily disposable items. After all, I could load up on tons of stuff, and who doesn't love a deal? What I didn't realize is that I was throwing money away! Times have changed, and I've grown to value quality over quantity. I love the quality of the clothes from New York & Co! My only gripe is that I am between sizes on the jackets, but I have this issue everywhere. Finding a fabulous tailor is next on my to do list.

The sales associates at the Eastridge location are super friendly, helpful, and honest. The girls have helped me get the most value out of my purchases on numerous occasions, which has caused me to spend a little more than I usually would. The coupons are fabulous! Be sure to shop the buy 1, get 1 50% off sales, and bring those coupons for even deeper discounts! $50 off of a $100 purchase, and the $100 off of a $200 are examples of the type of savings I'm taking about. Sign up online to receive coupons and notifications of sales.

You're welcome.







HIGHLIGHTS: affordable styles

My shopping experience here started out good, but turned sour. I liked the fact that I was able to get a couple of shirts at an affordable price but at checkout the girl was super pushy and asked me 3 times (after I'd told her "no thank you" each time) if I wanted to apply for their damn credit card. How many different ways can I politely say NO. I won't be returning to this store. I didn't catch her name, but her cashier ID is 338735. Be aware of the pushy sales associate!







I usually don't leave review unless I really feel like it's necessary. For a place that I usually shop at and had good services, this time it was poorly given, especially by the store manager name Daisy/Deisy. 

I know holidays are really hectic and busy. Regardless of it, that doesn't mean you service your customers poorly. I went shopping here on 12/21, main reason was to make a return, but I ended up shopping. I switched my purse and wallet out few days ago and left my NYC credit card in my other wallet. My mom and I ended up doing some shopping here and since I had the $20 reward, which required me to use my NYC credit card. the line was long with only one register available. I patiently waited for a good amount of 20-30 mins. By the time it was my turn, Daisy/Deisy had the biggest face ever without a smile! Hey! I know you were probably tired and drained from the customers, but the customers are also tired and drained from a long day at work and having to go to the mall for last minute presents and waiting in line. Everyone is tired, I don't think you should give a big cranky face at the customers. I asked her if she can look up my account since I don't have my card on me. She called my account and loudly asked me to give her my last 4 digits of my social and repeated it loudly on the phone where other customers heard it. She wasn't happy making the call and at the end she told this store will No LONGER look up account for security purpose and if I want to shop here I would need my card. I know that many stores like Macy's, Nordstrom, JCPenney, and even Target would gladly call to look up for your account. Even at the other Ny&c in Oakridge Mall. Most stores even ask you to write your last 4 digits down on paper for security purpose instead of repeating it loudly along with my numbers. I asked her since when was this implemented and she said "now,"  with a big attitude tone to it. I asked her what's your name and she said "Daisy, I'm the store manager." Definitely a store manager with a big attitude. Regardless you are a store manager or a sales associate, that doesn't mean you give poor customer service and my purchase was over $130. There wasn't a smile on her face throughout the whole purchase, which I honestly think it matters for customer service. I waited for a long time in line and she looked mad. I don't care if you are store manager, but if you are then you need to ensure customers satisfactory and the store runs well for the holidays. I never had this experience before and I had also enjoyed shopping here!! Horrible experience ever! Especially coming from a store manager who doesn't understand what customer service is.







I bought a pair of pants here during their 50% off sale shortly after Thanksgiving weekend.  The jeans were "originally $60."  My ass, they were not that great of quality, but $30 was decent because they fit well.  When I brought them home and tried them on again, I realized they had a real chemical smell that made me nauseous.  I tried to wash them, but they still smelled!  On the third wash the color was completely faded and they STILL SMELLED.  I even washed them with vinegar.  Yeah, $60 my ass.

Also the girl at the counter was SOOOOOO rude. I can't even believe it.  I almost left the pants at the counter.  It should have been a sign to leave the pants there.  She wanted me to sign up for a credit card or something and I declined and she pushed again and I declined.  After that she asked me to donate to some charity and when I declined she pushed again.  I declined again and SHE PUSHED.  Who does that?  She got me to round up my purchase and donate a few measly cents to this charity.  She seriously ticked me off.  I am never going to this store again.







Worst NY&C ever! Worst customer service in store and their platinum service on the phone.  Especially the customer service representative JENNY I spoke with 4/4/16 from the Eastridge store. Of course this was after I had to use my own phone to call because the manager on duty said they don't call customer service for their customers she then preceeded to give me a bogus number that didn't allow you to speak to anyone in customer service,  just directed you to their website.  I had to look on the back of my platinum card to find a number where you can speak with a horrible, distespectful representative. This company treats people with disabilities like they are trash. They could truly care less. I have been a customer for over 30 years.  But I will never shop with them again.  They have lost my business forever!  I highly recommend shopping at Macy's,  they have excellent customer service and always have good deals.  They actually listen and try to assist their customers.  My best recommendation NEVER shop at a  New York and Company store or their website. This was the first day I was actually physically able to shop, they made what should have been a super happy day for me a stressful,  depressing shopping experience.







The service here is C grade.   I can't say much about their entire clothing line
because I have not bought much from them.  However, I was very disappointed with the supposedly leather belt that I bought from this store.  When I pointed out a couple of scratches on the belt to the clerk at the checkout counter, she looked at me straight in the eyes and adamantly said that they a natural thing for leather products.  To my amazement, the belt broke into two pieces two weeks after purchase.  I demand to know  from New York Company the source of manufacturing and a refund.







I get that they have long pants and jeans but what about the short and the skinny???

I can't fit their xsmall here. Its too bad. They have so many cute clothes especially for work/career. They have suits and comfy casuals. Great accessories as well. Definitely for the "adult" in you. I just wished I fit their clothing. 

I will continue looking and dressing like a 15 year old.







3.5 stars.

New York & Co. is where I shop to find work clothes :) They have a great selection on business and casual attires and in the end, it all comes out to a very affordable amount. I say "in the end" because they always have deals where they take certain percentages off a certain amount purchased.

For example, my mom and I shopped here last week. bought like 3 items and 2 pairs of socks and it already came out to a little over $100! Pretty pricey for me... but I got a discount because I pulled up my email from NY&Co giving me $40 off any purchase over $90... woohoo! My mom was able to get the same discount on her clothes, too.

Even if you don't shop here very often (or even at all) and you're not interested in signing up for an account (which gives you even more discounts/savings), it's totally ok - they ALWAYS have some kind of deal going on right in the store. No coupons, necessary.

It was already a 9:20 PM (20 minutes after they've already closed) when we finished our purchase and the lady helping us was super nice and patient! Thank you to her!... and thank you to the other associate who played Glee songs when the store was about to close - I'll admit, I started head bobbing, singing, and grooving a little while I was in the fitting room!







As a girl who stands 5'10" and is not quite as round as she is long, it can be a real challenge for me to find pants that will fit me properly. They are always either too baggy a hips or too dern short, but not at New York & Company. This has been my go to place for jeans and other assorted pants for quite a few years now for a variety of reasons. One, because their tall pants are the perfect height and make me happy =P. Two, because they have several different cuts and washes of jeans that are all great on me. And three, because they have incredible sales! 

And by incredible I mean incredible, this weekend I meandered into the store and saw that they were having a pant sale for 4.99. Jeans for $11 and kakhi pants for 4.99! And these are not the cheaply made pants that are going to wear out on you by the 3rd wash. So you can be sure that I stocked up on all my pant needs this weekend =)

So why only 3 stars? Because I really don't use this store for anything other than their good deals on pants.







I shop here for one thing and one thing only: LONG pants and jeans.

Sure, it's great being tall. At 5'11, I can reach things off of high shelves without help, see over people at concerts, go without heels, etc.

There is one MAJOR drawback though, and it's that I can hardly ever find pants that are long enough! If I buy regular pants, they end up looking like clam-diggers, and I end up looking like a nerd. Basically, I need at least a 34" inseam, which is hard to come by in women's clothing.  

NY & Co. has a decent selection (about 4 or 5 styles) of pants that fit me, so even if I can't stand the rest of the stuff in the store, I can walk in and be comforted in knowing that I can walk out in a decent pair of jeans, ankles unexposed to the world.







I live north of downtown and usually shop at Valley Fair or Oakridge.  Today I wanted to shop at 3 stores in particular and VF is the only other mall in the area that has all 3.  I was not about to hit up VF on a Saturday afternoon so I went on a little adventure to the east side!  

Yay! This location is great!  

The store was in great shape for a Saturday afternoon.  Even the clearance section was nicely organized!  I tried on a few things and a friendly sales girl helped me find additional sizes and even called around to other stores for me - I'll while being super sweet about it.  

If I need to shop at NY&Co I'll come to this location before hitting up Oakridge for VF.







RUDE, RUDE AND RUDE.  Everytime I go to this store, no one is greeting the customers and there are at least three workers standing around doing nothing.  Maybe rearranging the jewelry.  They are no help.  You have to ask them for help and they just give a look like "what"?  I shop at  Ann Taylor Loft.  Way nicer clothes and priced around the same.  Don't bother with this store unless you don't want help.







I love this store! They have really cute accessories, and nice professional, but stylish, work clothes. The staff is always very helpful and friendly.







            New York & Company.
        






