        2/16/2011
    








1 check-in
        


3.5 stars.New York & Co. is where I shop to find work clothes :) They have a great selection on business and casual attires and in the end, it all comes out to a very affordable amount. I say "in the end" because they always have deals where they take certain percentages off a certain amount purchased.For example, my mom and I shopped here last week. bought like 3 items and 2 pairs of socks and it already came out to a little over $100! Pretty pricey for me... but I got a discount because I pulled up my email from NY&Co giving me $40 off any purchase over $90... woohoo! My mom was able to get the same discount on her clothes, too.Even if you don't shop here very often (or even at all) and you're not interested in signing up for an account (which gives you even more discounts/savings), it's totally ok - they ALWAYS have some kind of deal going on right in the store. No coupons, necessary.It was already a 9:20 PM (20 minutes after they've already closed) when we finished our purchase and the lady helping us was super nice and patient! Thank you to her!... and thank you to the other associate who played Glee songs when the store was about to close - I'll admit, I started head bobbing, singing, and grooving a little while I was in the fitting room!




