        9/4/2008
    

As a girl who stands 5'10" and is not quite as round as she is long, it can be a real challenge for me to find pants that will fit me properly. They are always either too baggy a hips or too dern short, but not at New York & Company. This has been my go to place for jeans and other assorted pants for quite a few years now for a variety of reasons. One, because their tall pants are the perfect height and make me happy =P. Two, because they have several different cuts and washes of jeans that are all great on me. And three, because they have incredible sales! And by incredible I mean incredible, this weekend I meandered into the store and saw that they were having a pant sale for 4.99. Jeans for $11 and kakhi pants for 4.99! And these are not the cheaply made pants that are going to wear out on you by the 3rd wash. So you can be sure that I stocked up on all my pant needs this weekend =)So why only 3 stars? Because I really don't use this store for anything other than their good deals on pants.




