        1/6/2008
    








First to Review
        


I shop here for one thing and one thing only: LONG pants and jeans.Sure, it's great being tall. At 5'11, I can reach things off of high shelves without help, see over people at concerts, go without heels, etc.There is one MAJOR drawback though, and it's that I can hardly ever find pants that are long enough! If I buy regular pants, they end up looking like clam-diggers, and I end up looking like a nerd. Basically, I need at least a 34" inseam, which is hard to come by in women's clothing.  NY & Co. has a decent selection (about 4 or 5 styles) of pants that fit me, so even if I can't stand the rest of the stuff in the store, I can walk in and be comforted in knowing that I can walk out in a decent pair of jeans, ankles unexposed to the world.




