2329 Stoneridge Mall RdPleasanton, CA 94566


        (925) 225-0395
    






This is definitely my go to store of choice of all of the locations near me. 

The store is always very well organized, lots of choices of sizes, and the staff is always extremely friendly & welcoming! You can always count on a team member being on the floor to offer assistance & offer a fitting room if needed. Line is moved quick at checkout. 

The only con I can say is, the fitting rooms can use a little sprucing up. They are clean, but missing a majority of the hooks to hang up your clothes or purse. Other than that, two thumbs up for sure!







NY & Co you might want to inform your new employees who chose to close the dressing rooms at 825 when the store is open to 9 that they are hurting your profits. After being a loyal weekly shopper for over 8 years tonight I took my business across the way to Banana Republic because your employee literally rolled her eyes and scrunched her nose when myself and another customer questioned why All dressing rooms were closed? In addition, BR employees apologized for your employees lack of service. That's how you grow your profits!







The Most pathetic brand and store, I have ever seen..... I order an item online, and but didn't like it because of improper fitting. I called the store and the "first lie" they told me, that I cannot return the product online and I have to come personally to store to return it. When I went to store they gave me store credit. The "second lie" they told me that I can gift that card to anyone if I don't want to use it, whereas that card strictly says "This card is a non-transferable card" and the "biggest lie" was they told me that I can use that card for online purchase. When I was trying to add that card to my account, I couldn't add it, because it can only be used in stores. "STOP ANNOYING PEOPLE, IF YOU GUYS DOESN'T HAVE KNOWLEDGE, THEN DON'T TALK BULLSHIT AND STOP LYING". 

I called and spoke with the store manager named "Victoria" and she said that she can do an exception of changing the store credit to a gift card, which I can use it online, let's see how much truth it is. Will keep you guys posted, in the meantime, please be aware of their stupid and pathetic policies and lies.







I love this store they always have great deals and quality clothes. I called the Pleasanton location this morning using the app on my phone looking for black sailor pants with the buttons on the front. I spoke to Victoria and I inquired about these pants she found them in my size along with a couple of sweaters that I was looking for. She told me she would put them on hold for me to pick up this afternoon. She also looked up a couple of other items I was looking for. They weren't a available, but it's cool since I can get these online. I came in as planned and Victoria had everything  ready that I wanted to purchase. I found a nice sweater for $7.00. The other lady Daysha who took over for Victoria to finish ringing me up noticed their was a red stain on it and immediately assisted me with picking a duplicate of this sweater without the stain. Great looking out because not everyone pays attention to detail when ringing up customer purchases. This sweater works well for me since I work in the city and you never know about the weather. Plus it will come in handy if the rain returns. Victoria and Daysha were very professional and helpful. I'm happy with my purchases.  I spent $48.15 saved $105.88 today. Woo who!







This is my go to store for work clothes. I'm probably here at least once a month and always get great service. The employees are friendly and helpful when I have a question or need to use the dressing rooms. The store is also usually super clean and organized. I also looooove all their sales. The only downfall is walking in and wearing the same clothes that are hanging on the rack. Talk about moded! Lol







It's been a while since I visited this location, but after walking in the store, I realized why. I was the first customer to enter once the employee rolled up the gate. As I entered, the staff looked me in my face and did not greet me or anything. I couldn't even get a good morning. Shortly after, another customer enters and words were exchanged by the same employee. I assume this customer was greeted. At that moment, I wanted to walk out of the store. Unfortunately, this is the only place of business that has the clothing I need to purchase at this mall. I grabbed some clothes to try on and approached another employee, Brianna, for her assistance. She was very helpful and friendly. She assisted me in picking out the proper size of clothing with no hesitation. Now that it's time to pay the bill, there's the initial employee at the register, now wanting to have a conversation. I really did not feel like speaking to her at this point. She rang up my purchase, which totaled almost $160. On my way out, I stopped Brianna and told her that she was the reason why I chose not to walk out of the store. It was because of her that I didn't walk out and go to another mall. Please know that something like a greeting can go a long way.







I love this store because of their designs. I work at doctors office, so I always need to be dressed in semi-formal attire. Everything in this store (minus the athletic wear) I can definitely wear to work! 

Black Friday sales are good too on top of that they have sales literally from end of Nov to early Jan. 

Lots of differently sizes (petite, long, regular)  which is very nice, but its hard to find my size because I'm petite and everyone Asian girl in the Bay Area is too. :)







I'm writing in regards to the location in the Sun Valley mall. I am not crazy about going to the Sun Valley mall however they do have some nice shops in there.


I have been coming here for years, there clothes are not top quality though quality enough and seem to last fairly long.

This particular store always seems to have a great selection of sharp, modern style chic clothes all the way from casual nice, sharp looking work wear clothes and a descent selection of going out clothes and best of all they have a petite section.

Store is bright and clean. Good service are a hit and miss here like any department store. Today service was especially helpful. There is Limited amount of Fitting rooms  though they are bright and large with GOOD LIGHTING a +...lol they have a descent selection of nice sharp new edge jewelry (don't last particular long being a little cheap) shoes look a little on the cheaper side. As for everything else is stylish comfortable and seems to last pretty long depending how you care for  it.

Prices can be a little expensive however they are always having a lot of great sales.







Have never been disappointed from the collection they have, have never walked out empty handed.







I used to work here. My whole side of the women in the family shop here. It used to be a good experience everytime I walk in there, but I think that EVERYBODY should work as one and everything should be divided evenly in work. The clothes have a more younger look, but it is nice. Plus there is ALWAYS sales! :) Overall, everything is usually good for a customer shopping experience with the right employees. I would recommend NYC







I have to give 2 stars because it's very clean and organized inside.  However, they need to restock their sizes frequently.







I'm a loyal customer and have been shopping there for years (in the serramonte one though).  I only go there twice a year, June and December, when the sales are a score!!!  I don't go otherwise.  I used to work here when it was called Lerner NY and in most cases that's what i still call it.  

They have my size.  Petites, average and tall can shop here.  

It's just the current set up nowadays can be hard for the eyes.  They don't shelve their pants any more in descending order according to size and shape like they used to.  I haven't seen any jackets there either, which they had a whole section of when i worked there.







So...I've never really shopped here before, always just looked in the window. But my friend had a return so I mosey on in and of course found something to buy when I wasn't going to buy anything! A way cute raincoat that was black and white plaid AND is was 30% OFF! So how could I resist? It will be perfect for those surprise rain showers when I go to NYC in a few weeks and I'll definitely be stylin' now. And then a belt and a purse for 50% off so cute! And the girl behind the counter was really helpful and got me signed up for free coupons (so I'll come back and spend more money of course!) All in all the service was good and the sales girls very friendly and helpful. Some great sales and cute cute stuff....oh yeah I'll be back!







The Music at the store is too loud every time I go in. It makes for a frustrating  shopping experience. I feel like I can not hear myself think. I also think the  aisles are to small for  a stroller. I know that not everyp erson in the world has to shop with a stroller but I do and I wish the walkways were less hard to get threw. 

The sale racks int he back possibly clearance area is STUFFED with stuff. It make the shop look messy when you head back to the back of the store. There is nothing worse than a messy shop. It makes me feel frantic when I am shopping.

There are good deals to be had  when you shop there but it seems like I am struggling to find reason to go back anytime soon.







I have been coming to this place since high school every time i need a nice work shirt. So i have been in this store 3 times this month. The first two, i bought 1 shirt each time-- same style, different color, 40 dollars each. I bought the second one because i decided i didn't like the first one's color on me, but i didn't have it at the time to return. I came back the third time, coming out from san francisco where i live (i grew up in pleasanton, that's why i was out here the first two times) specifically to return this shirt with my receipt, even giving my boyfriend money for gas to drive me out here. 

I go in, tell the sales associate "i bought two of the same shirts, but decided i didn't like this color" and she scans my receipt and said "this shirt is not on this receipt." Shit, i grabbed the receipt for the second shirt! I explain politely that i live in san francisco and i grabbed the wrong receipt, could she just do the refund for this one.  She said no, offered me a 22 dollar refund instead and i said "fine, i am not coming out here from san francisco again" when the manager told me that there is one in san francisco. How could i have not known?! I looked for one on yelp and their website, there is one in san francisco? No... there is one in daly city. The sales associate had the nerve to tell me it would probably be easier to get to that one from where i live then to the pleasanton one. Bitch, what? This is what i said, "what am i gonna do, walk from the nearest SF bus stop to get to the daly city one?" Anybody who has lived for any amount of time in SF or Daly city knows how separate they are.

So i took by 22 dollar refund. Oh wait, no i didn't, they forgot to mention i only get store credit. Does anybody want it? Because i don't. Seriously, screw this place. 

Same shirt, different color. Thanks for giving me a good fuck, NY&C. Btw i bought the shirt for a job interview because i have been out of work since making the move to SF, buying these shirts put my bank account into double digits. Luckily i got the job... i get paid for the first time in 3 weeks, maybe i can use my store credit to buy food until then!!!







The clothes are v. inexpensive, and quite a few are cheaply made.  However, they have great sales (like everything is 50% off), so if you see something you like, don't you DARE pay full price.

When I went here, the customer service left much to be desired- we waited over 10 minutes in line (we were 4th from the register).

Bottom line: worth picking through; be prepared to wait if your'e shopping on a weekday afternoon.







Wow I'm so glad I decided to walk in this place today!  I was on my way to forever 21, as I usually walk right past this place because for some reason I thought it was for the more mature crowd.  hehe.  But I was also looking for something more professional today and decided to see what they have to offer.  They had a great sale going on and I think almost everything's on sale, like 50%!!!  The signs said selected styles, and at first I thought, oh another scam, just a few items are really 50%...  But I saw a shirt I really liked and it had no markings on it that it was on sale.  When I asked the register lady, which was super nice by the way, she said yup it's only 15!.  And the jewelry was only 5 bucks down from 30! That was selected styles, but others were 50% off.  I was really happy, and let's just say that this store unexpedtedly took up an hour of my 1.5 hour slot dedicated to forever 21!  If you want Express like clothes, but less workish and more daytime, AND  more affordable with a great staff, then come in here.  
Whoo hoo- got a pair of earrings, 2 neckalaces, a cuute belt, a nice button shirt, and a long white tunic for 50 bucks!







