        1/8/2016
    

It's been a while since I visited this location, but after walking in the store, I realized why. I was the first customer to enter once the employee rolled up the gate. As I entered, the staff looked me in my face and did not greet me or anything. I couldn't even get a good morning. Shortly after, another customer enters and words were exchanged by the same employee. I assume this customer was greeted. At that moment, I wanted to walk out of the store. Unfortunately, this is the only place of business that has the clothing I need to purchase at this mall. I grabbed some clothes to try on and approached another employee, Brianna, for her assistance. She was very helpful and friendly. She assisted me in picking out the proper size of clothing with no hesitation. Now that it's time to pay the bill, there's the initial employee at the register, now wanting to have a conversation. I really did not feel like speaking to her at this point. She rang up my purchase, which totaled almost $160. On my way out, I stopped Brianna and told her that she was the reason why I chose not to walk out of the store. It was because of her that I didn't walk out and go to another mall. Please know that something like a greeting can go a long way.




