        2/25/2011
    

I have been coming to this place since high school every time i need a nice work shirt. So i have been in this store 3 times this month. The first two, i bought 1 shirt each time-- same style, different color, 40 dollars each. I bought the second one because i decided i didn't like the first one's color on me, but i didn't have it at the time to return. I came back the third time, coming out from san francisco where i live (i grew up in pleasanton, that's why i was out here the first two times) specifically to return this shirt with my receipt, even giving my boyfriend money for gas to drive me out here. I go in, tell the sales associate "i bought two of the same shirts, but decided i didn't like this color" and she scans my receipt and said "this shirt is not on this receipt." Shit, i grabbed the receipt for the second shirt! I explain politely that i live in san francisco and i grabbed the wrong receipt, could she just do the refund for this one.  She said no, offered me a 22 dollar refund instead and i said "fine, i am not coming out here from san francisco again" when the manager told me that there is one in san francisco. How could i have not known?! I looked for one on yelp and their website, there is one in san francisco? No... there is one in daly city. The sales associate had the nerve to tell me it would probably be easier to get to that one from where i live then to the pleasanton one. Bitch, what? This is what i said, "what am i gonna do, walk from the nearest SF bus stop to get to the daly city one?" Anybody who has lived for any amount of time in SF or Daly city knows how separate they are.So i took by 22 dollar refund. Oh wait, no i didn't, they forgot to mention i only get store credit. Does anybody want it? Because i don't. Seriously, screw this place. Same shirt, different color. Thanks for giving me a good fuck, NY&C. Btw i bought the shirt for a job interview because i have been out of work since making the move to SF, buying these shirts put my bank account into double digits. Luckily i got the job... i get paid for the first time in 3 weeks, maybe i can use my store credit to buy food until then!!!




