        7/17/2007
    








First to Review
        


Wow I'm so glad I decided to walk in this place today!  I was on my way to forever 21, as I usually walk right past this place because for some reason I thought it was for the more mature crowd.  hehe.  But I was also looking for something more professional today and decided to see what they have to offer.  They had a great sale going on and I think almost everything's on sale, like 50%!!!  The signs said selected styles, and at first I thought, oh another scam, just a few items are really 50%...  But I saw a shirt I really liked and it had no markings on it that it was on sale.  When I asked the register lady, which was super nice by the way, she said yup it's only 15!.  And the jewelry was only 5 bucks down from 30! That was selected styles, but others were 50% off.  I was really happy, and let's just say that this store unexpedtedly took up an hour of my 1.5 hour slot dedicated to forever 21!  If you want Express like clothes, but less workish and more daytime, AND  more affordable with a great staff, then come in here.  Whoo hoo- got a pair of earrings, 2 neckalaces, a cuute belt, a nice button shirt, and a long white tunic for 50 bucks!




