        5/22/2007
    








First to Review
        


***March 13, 2008 Update***It pains me to do so...but I have to knock off a star.  I don't know what they're doing with their fashions...but it's got to stop!!!  The last 3 to 4 times I've been there I have found NOTHING that I wanted to buy.  NOTHING!  Please...the last thing anybody wants at the beginning of Spring is a black dress...so why do you have 4 different ones?!  Nobody is going to buy those!...and why is everything else white?!  Is white in fashion again?  When was all that white stuff in fashion?  I can't remember.***Original May 22, 2007 Review***New York & Company is supposedly the same as my all time favorite Lerner New York...but the last time I was at a Lerner NY it was still different.  Even though it's my favorite store, I walked in there prepared to give it a low rating because it's in ghetto mall and ghetto mall Gap is crap.Well, I just couldn't do it.  Yeah, in true ghetto mall fashion it has a little less selection than a normal NY&C...but it's really not bad.  The salespeople were really nice and helpful and I managed to find myself 2 tops, a skirt, and some jewelry.  Not bad for a Tuesday.This place reignited my love for NY&C so much that I almost bought a Coach knockoff purse that said NY NY NY all over it just to advertise for them.The corporation still hasn't gotten over that annoying habit of asking for your phone number every time you shop there though.  You'd think that class action lawsuit they lost would've done the trick...but apparently not.  Just say no when they ask.  It's all good.Did I mention I hate ghetto mall?




