2088 Newpark MallNewark, CA 94560


        (510) 818-1930
    






Hazel at the store was very helpful. She helped me pick up the right clothes for my close friends and my mom. Ask for Hazel. She's awesome!.







The ladies that work here are great! Very friendly & helpful. I love the options of clothes they have and they fit great







I normally don't get greeted at the store but when an associate is nearby they are always courteous. I love your clothes and enjoy shopping in this store. It's unfortunate that the other yelpers did not have a good experience but personally I enjoy the store.







Here are the reasons why I'm giving this place 3 stars: 

1. The store is organized and stocked with merchandise 
2. The styles are great 
3. They have Petite and Tall sizes 
4. The prices are affordable when it's on clearance 
5. The customer service isn't all that great... 
6. It's hard to find help, when you need it...... 
7. The fittings rooms aren't that clean (floor)..... 

Overall, I prefer to shop at Express than here.......







Alrighty, I've got some good and bad with this place:

Good:
- I really like most of their styles, and they have a good range of them too
-The prices are affordable and they are always offering specials/sales/and promotions 
-Their striped collared shirts are my fave...plus they have Tall size pants (and petite)...thank god!!!

Not so good:
- There's usually no employees located anywhere else in the store other than at the cash register.  If you have questions about merchandise or need a fitting room, take a number and get in line.
- While their prices are very affordable, as the saying goes...you get what you pay for.  I don't mean the apparel falls apart or anything, but a lot of the pants wrinkle pretty bad just from sitting down once, and the shirts are the same, even if you heavily starch them







***March 13, 2008 Update***
It pains me to do so...but I have to knock off a star.  I don't know what they're doing with their fashions...but it's got to stop!!!  The last 3 to 4 times I've been there I have found NOTHING that I wanted to buy.  NOTHING!  Please...the last thing anybody wants at the beginning of Spring is a black dress...so why do you have 4 different ones?!  Nobody is going to buy those!

...and why is everything else white?!  Is white in fashion again?  When was all that white stuff in fashion?  I can't remember.

***Original May 22, 2007 Review***
New York & Company is supposedly the same as my all time favorite Lerner New York...but the last time I was at a Lerner NY it was still different.  Even though it's my favorite store, I walked in there prepared to give it a low rating because it's in ghetto mall and ghetto mall Gap is crap.

Well, I just couldn't do it.  Yeah, in true ghetto mall fashion it has a little less selection than a normal NY&C...but it's really not bad.  The salespeople were really nice and helpful and I managed to find myself 2 tops, a skirt, and some jewelry.  Not bad for a Tuesday.

This place reignited my love for NY&C so much that I almost bought a Coach knockoff purse that said NY NY NY all over it just to advertise for them.

The corporation still hasn't gotten over that annoying habit of asking for your phone number every time you shop there though.  You'd think that class action lawsuit they lost would've done the trick...but apparently not.  Just say no when they ask.  It's all good.

Did I mention I hate ghetto mall?







I'm giving them 2 stars only because they have really nice clothes for work, however the restrictions on their coupons are insane. I went to the clearance section picked out a few items o liked tried them on and figured I'd take them since they were on red line marked down 70% off. I almost never pay full price for items here unless I really love the piece. So anyway I went to pay and asked her to ring up and check what the final prices on the items were, since they were on sale. She checked the prices and turned out they were only buy one get one half off bringing my total to $108 not including taxes! Mind you this was 1 shirt and 2 slacks, the cashier said they must have been miss racked that the price was correct but the sales rack they were on wasnt. Psh....I left the clothes there and said no thank you. Maybe I'll be back when the stockers learn how to do their jobs correctly and rack appropriately!







