        9/27/2013
    

I love shopping at the store but my online experience was not so favorable.  1st of all I was not able to use my coupon code for a lot of the things online. 2nd I received a confirmation for my ONLINE order and THAT'S IT!  I received an email that said I would receive my order in 5-7 days.  After 7 days past I went online to hunt for my order status.  When I attempted to check my order status it said the item was ordered THAT'S IT!  so, I had to call customer service and they advised me I had 1 item on backorder so that delayed my back whole order.  The lady on the phone was nice and apologetic and informed me that she released the rest of the order to be shipped.  I let her know that I was not happy that I had NO COMMUNICATION about the delay of my order or the fact that something was on back order.  The NYC online experience was not as good as JCP, Macy's or other online retail sites that send you lots of email concerning your order status. I could not find anything on YELP for their online shopping so that is why I am writing the review on the site. I like the store experience and hate the online experience.  Needless to say I will not shop online at NYC again.




