        11/13/2012
    








1 check-in
        









            Listed in Born to Shop


I got an online coupon for $50 off after spending $100 and I already had a gift card for $35 so i figured, I couldn't lose on this one.  Basically spend about $20 bucks out of pocket and get $100 worth in clothes.  I visited this NYC store and it was just sad.  Aside from the massive online coupons they sent out for Veterans day; they also had "cash rewards" sales... Their selection was very poor... they only had big  sizes on all pants and their sale merchandise was in complete disarray.  I managed to find a super cute raincoat and decided to try it out.  I didn't want to go into the fitting rooms and when I looked around for a mirror to try it out, i didn't see any!  No mirrors in a female clothing store!!! Are you SERIOUS?  They have more mirrors at Payless Shoes than they do at NYC???? I could not believe it.  I had to find a sales rep to ask her where the heck their mirrors where.  She pointed at two very slim mirrors on both sides of the store towards the fitting rooms.  I still needed to buy one more item because the raincoat was on sale and it didn't add up to the $100 so I decided to look at their skinny pants.  I saw some gray ones that were really nice and the smallest they had was a 2 but I needed a 0.  I looked in the black ones and found one but they were also discounted at buy one and get one for 50% off so i figured why not get the second pair.  When i asked a different sales rep if that's all the sizes they had on the gray ones and she said yes, she looked me up and down and said, "But we should have your size"  WTF does that mean!  If I asked her if that's all they had in sizes it is only fair to deduce that I DID NOT find the size I was looking for.  I just shook my head, grabbed a sweater instead and proceeded to pay my stuff.  People now a days are soooooo funny.  Just can't think outside the box.




























