        12/14/2011
    

I highly recommend not ordering anything from this store to be shipped to your house. I had wanted a sweater in size small and it was unavailable in store, but it was available online. The clerk offered to order it for me and have it shipped for a nominal fee (under $3). I thought that sounded convenient and gave her all of my information. When I received the confirmation email a few days later, I realized that the woman forgot to put in my apartment number. I called the customer service right away and was told that there was nothing they could do, since the item already shipped. She advised that I wait until the item was returned to them, call them back, and place a new order. That was irritating. I hadn't heard anything in a couple of days and couldn't access any shipping information online, so I called Customer Service again. This lady told me that I should have called UPS originally and that the first customer service clerk had advised me incorrectly. She told me to call USPS (apparently UPS transfers the package to USPS) and find out what happened. She was unapologetic for the series of errors and the amount of time I've wasted at work with this issue. I called USPS and found out that the item is already being shipped back to the sender. So now I will have to call NY & Co Customer Service yet again. At this point, there is no guarantee the same sweater will even be available. Had I known that the clerk at this store was a stupid moron who couldn't enter an apartment number, I would have just ordered it online myself. Save yourself the trouble and go shop somewhere else.Edited to add: I just spent 30 mins on the phone with NY & Co Customer Service and found out that the sweater is sold out and that I can't get it. I am so sad about this. It was such a unique color and it doesn't sound like the sweater will come back in stock.




